{"type":"message","id":"6a21875f","parentId":"27d59098","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:25:18.959Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9hykxwp0tau2_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 012215\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n2. There's a pending TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression)\r\n3. Next action is to implement TIC classifier on pulse log files\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step is to start implementing the TIC experiment. I should look at the existing pulse logs and start building the classifier.\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist in the sandbox, particularly in the logs directory and research directory.\r\n\r\nSince this is a fresh pulse (stateless discontinuous agent), I need to take ONE concrete action. The most logical next step based on the goals is to either:\r\n1. Look at the pulse logs to understand the data\r\n2. Create the initial TIC implementation\r\n3. Review existing research docs\r\n\r\nGiven that this is the first pulse after the session that established these insights, I should start by examining the pulse logs to understand the data structure before implementing the classifier.\r\n\r\nLet me take action to read/analyze the existing pulse logs to prepare for TIC implementation.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment is the next critical step, but I need to first understand the pulse log format and structure before implementing the classifier. The pulse_*.md files contain the raw data needed for classification.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nExamine recent pulse logs to understand their structure and content patterns, enabling the TIC classifier implementation. Create a preliminary analysis of log format for the invariant/variant classification task.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Experiment Prep - Pulse Log Analysis\r\nGenerated: 2026-03-24 0120XX\r\nPurpose: Prepare data structure for Temporal Invariance Compression classifier\r\n\r\n## Pulse Log Format Analysis\r\nBased on recent pulse logs (pulse_2026-03-24_*.md):\r\n\r\n### File Structure\r\n- Header: Pulse metadata (timestamp, iteration count)\r\n- ### OBSERVATION: 1-2 sentence situational awareness\r\n- ### ACTION: Concrete next step description\r\n- ### MUTATION: File edit block with old_text/new_text/file\r\n\r\n### Data Fields for TIC Classification\r\n1. **Observation text** - describes current state\r\n2. **Action text** - describes intended move\r\n3. **Mutation block** - the actual file change\r\n\r\n### Invariant Candidates (should remain stable across pulses)\r\n- File paths (research/, logs/, state/)\r\n- Goal structure (## headers, ### subheaders)\r\n- Action pattern (\"Examine\", \"Create\", \"Implement\", \"Review\")\r\n- Mutation format (old_text/new_text/file triple-backtick block)\r\n\r\n### Variant Candidates (should change between pulses)\r\n- Timestamps\r\n- Observation content\r\n- Action descriptions\r\n- Specific file names mentioned\r\n- Iteration counts\r\n\r\n## Next Step\r\nImplement TIC classifier in `src/tic_classifier.py` to:\r\n1. Extract invariants vs variants from pulse_*.md files\r\n2. Classify with target >70% accuracy\r\n3. Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n\r\n---\r\nfile: research/TIC-PREP.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 01:22:36\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774329918956}}
